Here is a comprehensive Technical Specifications document for the Quenne Smart University. This document is structured as a formal engineering blueprint, translating the conceptual architecture into measurable, implementable components, vendors, protocols, and performance metrics.

---

TECHNICAL SPECIFICATIONS: QUENNE SMART UNIVERSITY

Document ID: QSU-ARCH-001
Version: 2.0 (Final Build)
Classification: Infrastructure Master Plan

---

1.0 COGNITIVE CORE (ZONE 1) - HPC & QUANTUM SPECS

1.1 AI & Quantum Server Specifications

· Primary AI Compute Cluster:
  · Type: Hybrid GPU/TPU Pod.
  · Hardware: 256x NVIDIA H100 Tensor Core GPUs (or next-gen B200) interconnected via NVLink Switch.
  · Alternative/Supplement: 64x Google TPU v5 Pods for specific transformer model workloads.
  · Peak Performance: ~1 ExaFLOP (FP16) for AI training.
· Quantum Computing Division:
  · Type 1 (Superconducting): 2x IBM Quantum System Two (or equivalent), targeting 1,500+ qubits with enhanced coherence times.
  · Type 2 (Trapped Ion): 1x Quantinuum System Model H2, for high-fidelity logic and low error rates.
  · Quantum Volume: Target > 2^18.
· Neuromorphic Nodes:
  · Hardware: 10x Intel Loihi 2 or IBM TrueNorth racks.
  · Function: Real-time sensor fusion, olfactory/visual pattern recognition at the edge.
· Storage:
  · Type: Parallel File System (Lustre/GPUDirect).
  · Capacity: 50 PB raw, all-flash NVMe tier for checkpointing.
  · Speed: > 1 TB/s read/write.

1.2 Networking (The "Digital Nervous System")

· Backbone: 400G/800G Ethernet (IEEE 802.3df) with optical circuit switching.
· Interconnect: InfiniBand NDR (400Gb/s) for GPU-to-GPU communication (RDMA).
· Quantum Network (Q-LAN): Dedicated dark fiber for Quantum Key Distribution (QKD) between Zone 1 and Zone 2 (Quantum Labs) to ensure unhackable data transfer.

---

2.0 INTELLIGENT LEARNING SYSTEM (ZONE 3) - SPECS

2.1 AI Tutors

· Platform: Custom Large Language Model (LLM) based on Llama 3 or GPT-4 class architecture, fine-tuned on pedagogical datasets.
· Deployment: Hybrid Cloud/On-Prem.
· Capabilities:
  · NLP Accuracy: >95% intent recognition in 50+ languages.
  · Latency: <300ms response time.
  · Integration: LTI 1.3 standard for LMS (Canvas/Moodle) integration.

2.2 AR/VR Infrastructure

· Headsets:
  · High-End: Apple Vision Pro / Varjo XR-4 for medical/engineering simulation.
  · Scalable: Meta Quest Pro for general classroom use.
· Spatial Computing:
  · Engine: Unreal Engine 5.4 (Nanite/Lumen) for photorealistic renders.
  · Rendering: Cloud XR streaming from Zone 1 edge nodes to offload GPU work from headsets.
· Haptics: Integration with tactile gloves (e.g., HaptX) for robotics/medical labs.

---

3.0 AUTONOMOUS RESEARCH LABS (ZONE 2) - SPECS

3.1 Robotics Assistants

· Mobile Manipulators: 20x Boston Dynamics Spot with Stretch arm, or equivalent.
  · Payload: 5 kg per arm.
  · Battery: Hot-swappable, 90-minute runtime.
· Fixed Laboratory Arms: 10x Universal Robots UR20e (collaborative).
  · Precision: ±0.05 mm.
· Autonomy Stack: ROS 2 (Humble Hawksbill) running on local edge nodes with NVIDIA Jetson Orin AGX.

3.2 Quantum Labs Environment

· Cooling: Dilution refrigerators (Bluefors LD series) achieving <10mK for superconducting qubits.
· Vibration Isolation: Active pneumatic isolators with <1nm floor vibration.
· EMI Shielding: Mu-metal shielding to attenuate magnetic fields by >60 dB.

---

4.0 ENERGY AUTONOMOUS CAMPUS (ZONE 4) - SPECS

4.1 Generation & Storage

· Solar: 5 MW peak capacity (Bifacial panels + trackers).
· Hydrogen:
  · Electrolyzer: 2 MW PEM electrolyzer (e.g., Cummins HyPM) for green H2 production.
  · Storage: Type IV composite tanks at 350 bar, 1,000 kg capacity.
  · Fuel Cells: 500 kW stationary PEM fuel cells for baseload.
· Magnetic Harvesting:
  · Type: Resonant inductive coils embedded in roadways (Zone 5/Zone 3 transit paths).
  · Harvesting Potential: 10-20 kW per vehicle lane, capturing energy from braking/motion.

4.2 Microgrid Management

· Controller: SEL Real-Time Automation Controller (RTAC) with AI co-processor.
· Optimization: Quantum-inspired annealing algorithm (via Zone 1) running every 5 seconds to balance load.
· Voltage: 11 kV distribution ring main.

---

5.0 CAMPUS DIGITAL TWIN - SPECS

5.1 Simulation Engine

· Platform: NVIDIA Omniverse or AWS TwinMaker.
· Fidelity:
  · Geospatial: 3cm resolution via drone photogrammetry (updated weekly).
  · BIM Level: LOD 350 (building systems detail).
· Physics Engine: Real-time fluid dynamics for HVAC simulation, rigid body physics for robotics testing.

5.2 Data Integration

· Protocols: MQTT (for sensors), OPC-UA (for energy grid), RTSP (for video feeds).
· Update Rate:
  · Static Elements: Daily.
  · Dynamic Elements (people, vehicles): Real-time (<100ms latency).
  · Energy Flows: 1Hz sampling.

---

6.0 SENSORS & HARDWARE LAYER - FIELD SPECS

6.1 Environmental Sensing

· Air Quality: Particulate Matter (PM1, PM2.5, PM10), CO2, VOCs.
· Acoustic: MEMS microphones for occupancy detection (privacy-filtered, only counting, not recording speech).
· Light: Lux sensors for smart dimming (integration with Zone 4 energy savings).

6.2 Structural Health

· Fiber Bragg Gratings: Embedded in concrete (Zone 1 & 2 foundations) for strain/temperature monitoring.
· Vibration: Piezoelectric accelerometers on critical machinery.

6.3 Biometric/Access (Opt-in for personalized education)

· Wearables: Smart badges (UWB for indoor positioning, accuracy ±10cm).
· Facial Recognition: Edge-based, opt-in for classroom attendance/engagement (vector embedding only, no raw images stored).

---

7.0 CYBERSECURITY & ETHICAL AI GOVERNANCE

7.1 Architecture

· Zero Trust: Micro-segmentation between Zones.
· QKD: Quantum Key Distribution for data at rest in the Cognitive Core.
· Blockchain: Hyperledger Fabric for immutable audit logs of AI decision-making.

7.2 Governance Protocols

· Bias Auditing: Automated testing of AI models (Zone 3 Tutors, Zone 2 Experimentation) against protected classes, enforced via GitOps CI/CD pipeline.
· Explainability: LIME/SHAP frameworks required for all models impacting student grading or access.
· Human-in-the-Loop: Circuit breaker switches in Zone 1 allowing human authority (President/Dean) to physically isolate any AI subsystem.

